    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i just don't want to panic him unnecessarily if it's nothing. he actually feels a bit better now that he's rested for a second, and the tingling is almost gone. he's saying it's definitely just the jet lag. is there any way we can just monitor him at home for the night? maybe if we keep him hydrated and give him an aspirin, we can just see how he feels in the morning before making a big deal out of it?",
